      "writtenOn": "2020-09-25T20:40:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Re-reading this, the reinterpret_cast shouldn\u0027t be necessary? The goal of placement-new is to turn your untyped wad of memory into a T. This should hopefully work equally well:\n\n   new (fBytes) BlockData\n\nAnd if I\u0027m not wrong we should be able to use the built-in copy constructor:\n\n   *(new (fBytes) BlockData) \u003d data;",
