        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-25T20:40:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was assuming we\u0027d construct and destruct all the types, not switch between memcpy and placement-construction/destruction on a case-by-case basis. From a UB perspective, we don\u0027t have a valid object living inside fBytes until we construct something there.\n\nCan we do this? \n\n    *(new (fBytes) BoolLiteralData) \u003d data;\n\nThe codegen appears identical: https://godbolt.org/z/Mroj8r",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 106,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 106,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "49a3d5d014e26920da68be0426360c15589f5224",
